    <h1>4.x feature comparison</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <p><span class=3D"status-macro aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-current">CON=
TENT OF THIS PAGE IS UNDER REVIEW</span></p>
<p>This page represents a comparison between <strong>Legacy Stack<em>&nbsp;=
</em></strong>(aka "<em>4.x</em>" stack) vs <strong>Platform Stack</strong>=
 (previously referred to as "<em>Symfony</em>", "<em>new</em>" or "<em>6.x<=
/em>" stack); it will be updated as new features are added.&nbsp;Note: Feat=
ures mentioned on the black list <u>are still available in 5.x</u>, but via=
 legacy kernel so you will need to use "pure legacy" or a mixed setup using=
 "legacy fallbacks".&nbsp;</p>
<p>For a list of Symfony features supported out of the box, see <a href=3D"=
/display/EZP/Symfony+feature+status">here</a>.</p>
<p>For additional related topics see&nbsp;<a href=3D"/display/EZP/Legacy+co=
de+and+features">Legacy code and features</a> and&nbsp;<a href=3D"/pages/vi=
ewpage.action?pageId=3D2720567">Intro for eZ Publish 4.x/3.x developers</a>=
.</p>
<h2 id=3D"id-4.xfeaturecomparison-Knownexistingintegration(whitelist):">Kno=
wn existing integration (<strong><span style=3D"color: rgb(51,51,51);">whit=
e&nbsp;</span></strong>list):</h2>
