</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><strong>Core</strong></td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">&nbsp;</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">Rating</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">User Rating not currently supported by API (the =
service to deal with ratings, rating field type already exists), planned to=
 be implemented later when some convention for FieldType provided API's are=
 established.<br><br>Solutions from community exists for the missing functi=
onality: &nbsp;<a href=3D"https://packagist.org/packages/makingwaves/ezstar=
ratingbundle" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">https://packagist.or=
g/packages/makingwaves/ezstarratingbundle</a></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">Shop</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">No shop or field<span>(/data)</span> types relat=
ed to shop currently supported by API, see <a href=3D"/display/EZP/Releases=
">Known issues</a>. This is planned for "eZ Platform 1.x" or a release shor=
tly thereafter, it will most likely use parts of Sylus for this functionali=
ty.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">eZComment</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><a href=3D"https://github.com/ezsystems/ezcommen=
ts/" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">ezcomments</a> was replaced i=
n 5.2 with a <a href=3D"https://github.com/ezsystems/CommentsBundle" class=
=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">CommentsBundle</a> that will provide an=
 agnostic system to integrate 3rd party comment services. Out of the box su=
pporting Disqus and Facebook integration but can via custom integration als=
o work with other 3rd party systems (example: service, content model based =
comments or even ezcomments)</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">Content Editing</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">Content editing module is not impl=
emented yet, but custom needs can for instance be solved with <a href=3D"/d=
isplay/EZP/eZ+Publish+Public+API">Public API</a>+Symfony controllers or use=
 of <a href=3D"https://github.com/ezsystems/ez-js-rest-client" class=3D"ext=
ernal-link" rel=3D"nofollow">javascript REST client</a> + <a href=3D"/displ=
ay/EZP/eZ+Publish+REST+API">REST API</a>.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">Module Permissions</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">Controller / Bundle Permissions is=
 not fully integrated with eZ Publish Repository permission system yet, cur=
rently standard Symfony firewall rules need to be used. Public API however =
has full support for permissions and <a href=3D"/display/EZP/Limitations+re=
ference">limitations</a>, and is as of 5.2 known to support legacy most edg=
e cases.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">UrlAlias Routing</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">UrlAlias has the same model as bef=
ore and hence does not support routing directly to a bundle:controller:acti=
on</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">Workflow</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">Planned for future version, see Sh=
op. Simple workflows already possible by using Symfony evens and Public API=
 "Signals".</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);"=
>Information Collector</span></td>
